+Black+Slavery%3A+Changing+Attitudes+and+Related+Practices%2C+1830%E2%80%931865&amp;rft.aulast=Bringhurst&amp;rft.aufirst=Newell+G.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fgregkofford.com%2Fblogs%2Fnews%2Ffive-times-mormons-changed-their-position-on-slavery&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AJoseph+Smith%27s+views+on+Black+people" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-JSHamCurse-2"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-JSHamCurse_2-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-JSHamCurse_2-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFSmith1836" class="citation journal cs1">Smith, Joseph (April 1836). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.josephsmithpapers.org/paper-summary/letter-to-oliver-cowdery-circa-9-april-1836/2">"For the Messenger and Advocate"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/Messenger_and_Advocate" title="Messenger and Advocate">The Latter Day Saints' Messenger and Advocate</a></i>. <b>2</b> (7): 290 &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/The_Joseph_Smith_Papers" title="The Joseph Smith Papers">The Joseph Smith Papers</a>. <q>After having expressed myself so freely upon this subject [of slavery], I do not doubt, but those who have been forward in raising their voices against the South, will cry out against me .... It is my privilege then to name certain passages from the Bible, and examine the teachings of the ancients upon the matter as the fact is uncontrovertible [sic] that the first mention we have of slavery is found in the Holy Bible, pronounced by a man [Noah] who was perfect in his generation, and walked with God. And so far from that prediction being averse to the mind of God, it remains as a lasting monument of the decree of Jehovah, to the shame and confusion of all who have cried out against the South, in consequence of their holding the sons of Ham in servitude. 'And he said, Cursed be Canaan; a servant of servants shall he be unto his brethren.' ... (Gen. 9:25-26). Trace the history of the world from this notable event down to this day, and you will find the fulfillment of this singular prophecy. [T]he curse is not yet taken off from the sons of Canaan, neither will be until it is affected by as great a power as caused it to come; and the people who interfere the least with the purposes of God in this matter, will come under the least condemnation before Him ....</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Latter+Day+Saints%27+Messenger+and+Advocate&amp;rft.atitle=For+the+Messenger+and+Advocate&amp;rft.volume=2&amp;rft.issue=7&amp;rft.pages=290&amp;rft.date=1836-04&amp;rft.aulast=Smith&amp;rft.aufirst=Joseph&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.josephsmithpapers.org%2Fpaper-summary%2Fletter-to-oliver-cowdery-circa-9-april-1836%2F2&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AJoseph+Smith%27s+views+on+Black+people" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Marks-3"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Marks_3-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Marks_3-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Marks_3-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFStuart_Bingham2015" class="citation journal cs1">Stuart Bingham, Ryan (July 2015). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.jstor.org/stable/10.5406/jmormhist.41.3.22">"Curses and Marks: Racial Dispensations and Dispensations of Race in Joseph Smith's Bible Revision and the Book of Abraham"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/Journal_of_Mormon_History" class="mw-redirect" title="Journal of Mormon History">Journal of Mormon History</a></i>. <b>41</b> (3): 22–57. <a href="/wiki/Doi_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="Doi (identifier)">doi</a>:<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://doi.org/10.5406%2Fjmormhist.41.3.22">10.5406/jmormhist.41.3.22</a>. <a href="/wiki/JSTOR_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="JSTOR (identifier)">JSTOR</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.jstor.org/stable/10.5406/jmormhist.41.3.22">10.5406/jmormhist.41.3.22</a> &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/JSTOR" title="JSTOR">JSTOR</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Journal+of+Mormon+History&amp;rft.atitle=Curses+and+Marks%3A+Racial+Dispensations+and+Dispensations+of+Race+in+Joseph+Smith%27s+Bible+Revision+and+the+Book+of+Abraham&amp;rft.volume=41&amp;rft.issue=3&amp;rft.pages=22-57&amp;rft.date=2015-07&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.5406%2Fjmormhist.41.3.22&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F10.5406%2Fjmormhist.41.3.22%23id-name%3DJSTOR&amp;rft.aulast=Stuart+Bingham&amp;rft.aufirst=Ryan&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F10.5406%2Fjmormhist.41.3.22&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AJoseph+Smith%27s+views+on+Black+people" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Reeve_2015-4"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Reeve_2015_4-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Reeve_2015_4-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Reeve_2015_4-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Reeve_2015_4-3"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFReeve2015" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/W._Paul_Reeve" title="W. Paul Reeve">Reeve, W. Paul</a> (2015). <span class="id-lock-limited" title="Free access subject to limited trial, subscription normally required"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=95j4BQAAQBAJ"><i>Religion of a Different Color: Race and the Mormon Struggle for Whiteness</i></a></span>. New York, New York: <a href="/wiki/Oxford_University_Press" title="Oxford University Press">Oxford University Press</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-19-975407-6" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-19-975407-6"><bdi>978-0-19-975407-6</bdi></a> &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Google_Books" title="Google Books">Google Books</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Religion+of+a+Different+Color%3A+Race+and+the+Mormon+Struggle+for+Whiteness&amp;rft.place=New+York%2C+New+York&amp;rft.pub=Oxford+University+Press&amp;rft.date=2015&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-19-975407-6&amp;rft.aulast=Reeve&amp;rft.aufirst=W.+Paul&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3D95j4BQAAQBAJ&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AJoseph+Smith%27s+views+on+Black+people" class="Z3988"></span></span>
