<li id="cite_note-Neither_White_Nor_Black-14"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Neither_White_Nor_Black_14-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Neither_White_Nor_Black_14-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Neither_White_Nor_Black_14-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Neither_White_Nor_Black_14-3"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Neither_White_Nor_Black_14-4"><sup><i><b>e</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFBushMauss1984" class="citation book cs1">Bush, Lester E. Jr.; <a href="/wiki/Armand_L._Mauss" class="mw-redirect" title="Armand L. Mauss">Mauss, Armand L.</a>, eds. (1984). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20221001163611/http://signaturebookslibrary.org/neither-white-nor-black/"><i>Neither White Nor Black: Mormon Scholars Confront the Race Issue in a Universal Church</i></a>. Salt Lake City, Utah: <a href="/wiki/Signature_Books" title="Signature Books">Signature Books</a>. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-941214-22-2" title="Special:BookSources/0-941214-22-2"><bdi>0-941214-22-2</bdi></a>. Archived from <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://signaturebookslibrary.org/neither-white-nor-black/">the original</a> on October 1, 2022.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Neither+White+Nor+Black%3A+Mormon+Scholars+Confront+the+Race+Issue+in+a+Universal+Church&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City%2C+Utah&amp;rft.pub=Signature+Books&amp;rft.date=1984&amp;rft.isbn=0-941214-22-2&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fsignaturebookslibrary.org%2Fneither-white-nor-black%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AJoseph+Smith%27s+views+on+Black+people" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
